thoughts.reasoning_problem:
Context: A podcast is not a novel. [BG] If a person is born in American City, the person is American. [BG] If a book is novel and it is written by a person, then the person is a novel writer. Dani Shapiro is an American writer. Family History is written by Dani Shapiro. Family History is a novel written in 2003. Dani Shapiro created a podcast called Family Secrets. [BG] Boston is an American city.
Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Dani Shapiro is a novel writer.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
Novel(x) ::: x is a novel.
Podcast(x) ::: x is a podcast.
BornInAmericanCity(x) ::: x is born in American City.
American(x) ::: x is American.
Book(x) ::: x is a book.
WrittenBy(x, y) ::: x is written by y.
NovelWriter(x) ::: x is a novel writer.
AmericanWriter(x) ::: x is an American writer.
Created(x, y) ::: x created y.
Premises:
¬Podcast(novel) ::: A podcast is not a novel.
∀x (BornInAmericanCity(x) → American(x)) ::: If a person is born in American City, the person is American.
∀x ∀y ((Book(x) ∧ Novel(x) ∧ WrittenBy(x, y)) → NovelWriter(y)) ::: If a book is novel and it is written by a person, then the person is a novel writer.
AmericanWriter(daniShapiro) ::: Dani Shapiro is an American writer.
Book(familyHistory) ∧ WrittenBy(familyHistory, daniShapiro) ::: Family History is written by Dani Shapiro.
Book(familyHistory) ∧ Novel(familyHistory) ::: Family History is a novel written in 2003.
Created(daniShapiro, familySecrets) ∧ Podcast(familySecrets) ::: Dani Shapiro created a podcast called Family Secrets.
Conclusion:
NovelWriter(daniShapiro) ::: Dani Shapiro is a novel writer.
